               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Gadla Libānos “Vita of Libānos” (fols. 3ra–47va)&#xD; II) Taʾammǝra
                     Libānos “Miracles of Libānos”: 11 miracles, preceded by a short praise to
                     Libānos (fols. 47vb–62vb[l.4])&#xD; III) Malkǝʾa Libānos “Image of Libānos”: 29
                     strophes (fols. 62vb[l.10]–65rb).</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <title ref="LIT6386Libanos"></title>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                        <locus from="3ra" to="47va"></locus>
                        <title type="complete" ref="LIT1473GadlaL#recension2"/>
                        
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
                        <locus from="47vb" to="62vb">fols. 47vb–62vb[l.4]</locus>
                        <title ref="LIT4717TaammerLi" type="complete">11 Miracles of Libānos</title>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2.0">
                           <locus target="#47va">47va, ls. 3-19</locus>
                           <title corresp="LIT4717TaammerLi#praise">praise in honour of the Saint </title>
                           <note>The Miracles are preceded by a short praise in honour of the Saint. It is written in a
                              smaller script but most probably by the same hand.</note>
                        </msItem>
                        <note>In the incipits of the Miracles, both names of the
                           protagonist (Libānos and Maṭāʿ) are alternatively used.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <note>Lacuna between Text II and Text III (<locus target="#62vb">62vb</locus>,
                        ls. 4-9).</note>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.3">
                        <locus from="62vb" to="65rb">fols. 62vb[l.10]–65rb</locus>
                        <title type="incomplete" ref="LIT3097RepCh377">Malkǝʾa Libānos “Image of Libānos”</title>
                        <note>29 strophes: one strophe is missing from the version edited in 
                           <bibl><ptr target="bm:Bausi2003Libanos"/><citedRange>206-212 (text) = 119-122 (tr.)</citedRange></bibl>), one strophe at the end is
                           missing.</note>
                        <note>The ultimate portion is written on the first (unruled) leaf
                           of quire B, probably by the hand different from that of the main text (hand
                           a).</note>
                     </msItem>
                  </msItem>
                  
